     <h1>Ways To Give</h1> 
     <h3>Phonathon Pledges</h3> 
     <p>Thank you for pledging during the Student Phonathon! Phonathon pledges can be fulfilled using the <a href="https://secure.westmont.edu/forms/giving/donation_form/newdonationform.html">Online Donation Form</a>. If you have a question or would like to request a pledge reminder, <a href="mailto:annualfund@westmont.edu">email the office of annual giving.</a></p> 
     <h3>Will your employer double your gift?</h3> 
     <p>Your employer may offer a match for your charitable contributions! <br> Click <a href="http://www.matchinggifts.com/westmont/">here</a> to find out more.</p> 
     <h3>Give Online</h3> 
     <p>Welcome to Westmontâ€™s online giving form. With our secure server, investing in Westmont has never been easier. Just point and click, and your gift - whatever its size - will help Westmont provide students with an excellent liberal arts education rooted in Christ. <a href="https://secure.westmont.edu/forms/giving/donation_form/newdonationform.html">Online Donation Form</a></p> 
     <h3>By Mail</h3> 
     <p>Make checks payable to Westmont College with any specific gift designation noted in the memo line. Westmont will issue an official receipt soon after receiving your gift. Checks can be mailed to:</p> 
     <p>Westmont College<br> Office of College Advancement<br> 955 La Paz Road<br> Santa Barbara, CA 93108</p> 
     <h3>Credit Cards</h3> 
     <p>Westmont is able to accept gifts of Visa or Mastercard.<br> In addition to making a credit card gift online using the <a href="https://secure.westmont.edu/forms/giving/donation_form/newdonationform.html">online donation form</a>, you can also call Audra Pearce, Gift Processor, at 805.565.7053. When calling, if you need to leave a message, please include:</p> 
     <ul> 
      <li>Your name</li> 
      <li> Account number</li> 
      <li>Exp. date</li> 
      <li>Gift amount</li> 
      <li>Purpose of gift </li> 
      <li>Visa or MasterCard</li> 
      <li>Daytime phone number</li> 
     </ul> 
     <h3>Monthly Giving &amp; Electronic Fund Transfer (EFT)</h3> 
     <p>Choose one of two ways to have gifts automatically sent to Westmont :</p> 
     <ul> 
      <li> Electronic fund transfer from your bank account</li> 
      <li>Automatic credit card debit from your credit account.</li> 
     </ul> 
     <p>To enroll in either option, complete the <a href="https://secure.westmont.edu/forms/giving/donation_form/newdonationform.html">online donation form</a> <strong>or</strong> fill out the printable enrollment form below and mail to:</p> 
     <p>Westmont College<br> Office of College Advancement<br> 955 La Paz Road<br> Santa Barbara, CA 93108</p> 
     <p><a href="documents/enrollment-form.pdf">Printable Enrollment Form</a></p> 
     <h3>Memorials and Tributes</h3> 
     <p>E-mail questions regarding memorials and tributes to the <a href="mailto:mdombek@westmont.edu">director of advancement systems.</a></p> 
     <h3>Stocks and Other Appreciated Assets</h3> 
     <p>For details on how to make a gift of stock, click here: <a href="how-to-give-stock.html">How to Give a Gift of Stock to Westmont College</a>. Also, you can e-mail questions about giving stocks and appreciated assets to the <a href="mailto:mdombek@westmont.edu">director of advancement systems.</a></p> 
     <h3>IRA Rollover</h3> 
     <p>If you are over age 70.5, you can rollover up to $100,000 annually from your IRA to Westmont . These gifts can be made tax-free and will help balance your IRA value with other estate assets. Depending upon your income level, there may be additional income tax benefits. Contact us at <a href="mailto:giftplanning@westmont.edu"><font color="#660000">giftplanning@westmont.edu</font></a> to explore this wonderful opportunity. To read more, please click <a href="http://pdf.giftlegacy.com/ebros/gleg_ebroch_download.pdf?WebID=GL2001-0008&amp;num=14#page=2" title="http://pdf.giftlegacy.com/ebros/gleg_ebroch_download.pdf?WebID=GL2001-0008&amp;num=14#page=2"><font color="#660000">here</font></a>.</p> 
     <h3>Westmont Employees</h3> 
     <p>Westmont employees can also give through payroll deduction. To access the online form to create or modify your deductions, <a href="http://webapps.westmont.edu/cgi-bin/WebObjects/facstaff.woa/wa/login" title="Faculty/Staff Directory">open the faculty/staff directory </a>and use the login feature in the middle of the screen. </p> 
     <!-- InstanceEndEditable --> 
